  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Exercise consultation, an intervention approach based on the transtheoretical model has been
      successful in promoting physical activity (PA) among adults. It is unknown whether this
      approach would be efficacious with youth. The purpose of this pilot study was to assess
      whether exercise consultation would increase PA levels and improve anthropometric measures
      and metabolic markers in obese adolescents.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
